# I use arr as your vals, d as your idxs
def remove(self, val):
        if self.d[val]:
            p = self.d[val].pop()
            last = self.arr[-1]
            self.arr[p] = last
            self.d[last].add(p)
            self.d[last].remove(len(self.arr)-1)

def remove(self, val):
        if self.indexes[val]:
            idx=self.indexes[val].pop()
            temp_val=self.vals[-1]
            self.vals[idx]=temp_val
            self.indexes[temp_val].add(idx)
            self.indexes[temp_val].discard(len(self.vals)-1)
